/mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Ugn3h", "text": "<math><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>G</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "As in case of elliptic orbit of a satellite mechanical energy<br /><br />remains constant, at any position of satellite in the orbit,<br /><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> ...(i)<br /><br />Now, if at position <math><mi>r</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>v</mi></math> is the orbital speed of satellite<br /><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&#160;</mi></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> ...(ii)<br /><br />So, from Eqs. (i) and (ii), we have<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi>